a child with rectal bleeding what could it be my year is having bleeding with bowel the toilet bowl is red what could be happening it could mean a lot of things but it is alarming and hence you should take your child to the doctor rectal bleeding in children could result from constipation or passage of very hard stools a viral or bacterial infection which is invasive to the intestines this might sound strange but yes sexual abuse should also be looked into may be rare in children but rectal cancer or other malignancies in the intestine intususception or the telescoping of the bowels into its own lumen which is rare in your nine year old could be an early sign of any blood disorder such as low platelets or leukemia please don't be alarmed but please i advice you to bring your child to a pediatrician and have all the work up and tests done as soon as possible Colorectal cancer Coeliac disease Crohn's disease Cancer Diarrhea Stomach cancer Constipation Fecal incontinence Diverticulosis Prostate cancer Urinary incontinence Irritable bowel syndrome Laxative Acute myelogenous leukemia Platelet Endometrial cancer Human feces Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Hemorrhoid Acute lymphoblastic leukemia Ulcerative colitis Wiskott-Aldrich syndrome Cervical cancer Cirrhosis Rectum Gastroenteritis Von Willebrand disease Folic acid Colonoscopy Escherichia coli O157:H7 Familial adenomatous polyposis Ovarian cancer Myelodysplastic syndrome Pneumonia Autoimmune diseases Group A streptococcal infection Muscle Gonorrhoea Glycogen storage disease type I Complete blood count Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome Ebola Schistosomiasis Ascariasis Gastrointestinal stromal tumor Small intestine Chronic fatigue syndrome Whipworm Lumbar puncture Bowel obstruction Stroke Sigmoidoscopy Chlorpromazine Autistic enterocolitis Malignant melanoma Dietary fiber AIDS Anemia Thrombocytopenia Traumatic brain injury Vitamin C Chemotherapy Atherosclerosis Idiopathic thrombocytopenic purpura Anal sex Blood Intussusception D